      <paragraph>
        <num>78.</num>
        <content>
          <p>Based on earlier view that small and micro-businesses familiarise on a case-by-case basis we include these costs as part of the recurring administrative costs and assess these to see if the smallest firms bear a disproportionate burden. Table 14 below shows how the total annual costs are split between different sized firms for each option. </p>
